# LearnFlow E-Learning Platform

LearnFlow is a full-stack e-learning platform built with the technologies you listed:

- Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
- Backend: Node.js and Express
- Database: SQL and MySQL
- API style: RESTful API
- Python: utility script for exporting seed course data

The app includes course search, authentication, enrollment, and a learner dashboard. It also runs without MySQL by using demo memory data, which makes it easy to deploy a live demo.

## Features

- Responsive landing and course catalog UI
- Search and category filtering
- Login and registration with hashed passwords
- JWT-based API authentication
- Course enrollment endpoint
- Learner dashboard with progress
- MySQL schema and seed data
- Python CSV seed export utility

## Project Structure

```text
api/index.js             Vercel serverless entrypoint
database/schema.sql      MySQL table definitions
database/seed.sql        Sample users, courses, and enrollments
public/                  HTML, CSS, and browser JavaScript
scripts/seed_courses.py  Python seed export script
src/app.js               Express REST API
src/db.js                MySQL connection pool
src/demoData.js          In-memory demo data
server.js                Local Node server entrypoint
```

## Run Locally

Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

Start the app:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Open:

```text
http://localhost:3000
```

Demo login:

```text
Email: learner@example.com
Password: password123
```

## Connect MySQL

Create the database and tables:

```bash
mysql -u root -p < database/schema.sql
mysql -u root -p < database/seed.sql
```

Copy `.env.example` to `.env`, then update the database values:

```text
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=3306
DB_USER=root
DB_PASSWORD=your_password
DB_NAME=learnflow
JWT_SECRET=your_long_secret
```

Restart the server after updating `.env`.

## REST API

```text
GET    /api/health
GET    /api/courses
GET    /api/courses/:id
POST   /api/auth/register
POST   /api/auth/login
POST   /api/courses/:id/enroll
GET    /api/me/enrollments
```

Authenticated routes require:

```text
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

## Python Utility

Export the starter course list to CSV:

```bash
npm run seed:python
```

The generated file is saved at `outputs/courses_export.csv`.

## Deployment

This project includes `vercel.json` and `api/index.js`, so it can be deployed to Vercel. Without MySQL environment variables, the deployed demo uses in-memory sample data.
